* Most Important Core Rules
  * All descriptions, comments, and messages must be written in English

* README Writing Rules
  * Always in English
  * Overview and Tutorial should be at the front
  * License content should be at the end
  * Do not automatically add detailed content, only add prompts asking me to add it
    * If content is mentioned as core in requirements, add a recommendation that it is core content and should be added

* Commit Message Rules
  * Write in summary format (overview style)
  * Use imperative mood (e.g., "Add feature", "Fix bug", "Update documentation")
  * Keep it concise and descriptive
  * First line should be 50 characters or less (if possible)
  * All commit messages must be in English
  * Example formats:
    * "Add user authentication feature"
    * "Fix agent registration bug"
    * "Update README with deployment instructions"
    * "Refactor version management module" 
